Name: smartSTPSysUp
Description: Indicates that the SmartSTP instance is up and active.

Name: smartSTPSysDown
Description: Indicates that the SmartSTP instance is shutting down.

Name: smartSTPModuleStatus
Description: Indicates whether an SS7 message queue is being monitored

Name: smartSTPAppStatus
Description: Indicates the status of an application.

Name: smartSTPLinkCO
Description: Indicates link change over/back

Name: smartSTPLinkRPO
Description: Indicates remote processor outage

Name: smartSTPLinkCong
Description: Indicates link congestion

Name: smartSTPLinksetFail
Description: Indicates indicates linkset failure

Name: smartSTPDestOutage
Description: Indicates destination point code unavailable

Name: smartSTPAdjPCOutage
Description: Indicates adjascent point code unavailable

Name: smartSTPPCMStatus
Description: Indicates PCM status (link up/down)

Name: smartSTPM3UAssocStatusNotif
Description: Indicates the status of an M3UA association

Name: smartSTPM3UASPStatus
Description: Indicates the status of an M3UA peer ASP

Name: smartSTPHeartbeat
Description: Sent periodically to indicate that Smart STP is alive

Name: smartSTPWatchPoolDeplete
Description: Sent to indicate that the TCAP BEGIN wacther pool is depleting

Name: smartSTPTCAPWatchEff
Description: Sent to indicate that too many TCAP BEGIN messages are timing out

Name: smartSTPRSILinkStatus
Description: Indicates the status of an RSI SIU link

Name: smartSTPSCCPDecodeFail
Description: Sent to indicate that too many SCCP decodes failed

Name: smartSTPTCAPDecodeFail
Description: Sent to indicate that too many TCAP decodes failed

Name: smartSTPUDTSThreshold
Description:
Sent to indicate that for too many messages no match was found in the routing table
and subsequently UDTS were sent

Name: smartSTPResyncTrap
Description: Emitted before and after a trap resynchronization process

Name: smartSTPCicStateChange
Description: Sent when CICs in an ISUP circuit group get blocked or unblocked

Name: smartSTPSCTPAssocStatusNotif
Description: Indicates the status of an SCTP association

Name: smartSTPSCTPPathStatusNotif
Description: Indicates the status of an SCTP association path

Name: smartSTPLicenseCongestion

Name: smartSTPGCTCongestion
Description: Indicates GCT Environment condition state

Name: smartSTPDSIBoardEvent
Description: Indicates Dialogic Board Status:ResetOK or Failed
